---
title: One-Pan Turkey Stir-Fry Tacos with Tangy Slaw, Sriracha Mayo & Fried Onions
description: We’re always up for a sweet and savory dinner pairing, and these tacos are just that. Ground pork and green pepper are cooked in a sweet soy glaze until sticky and tender. They’re stuffed into steamy tortillas, along with a tangy, cilantro-flecked cabbage slaw. Of course, we’d never skip out on taco toppings, and these ones don’t disappoint: There’s creamy, spicy Sriracha mayo and crispy fried onions. It’s all ready in just 15 minutes—life is sweet (and savory), friends.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/61a7d10f1f519f690151b006-f6138b25.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-turkey-stir-fry-tacos-61a7d10f1f519f690151b006-d3e74cfd.pdf
servings: 2
time required: 15 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-turkey-stir-fry-tacos-61a7d10f1f519f690151b006
cuisine: Asian
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 900 kcal
